{"title":"Tokenizer walkthrough: peek/consume API","gitnotes":1,"type":"markdown","body":"## Reading order\n\n1. Skim `Tokenizer` constructor — input is immutable.\n2. Focus on `peek()` — recursive skip of whitespace is intentional.\n3. `consume()` advances only after returning the peeked token.\n\n| Method | Mutates cursor? | Returns |\n|--------|-----------------|--------|\n| `peek()` | sometimes (WS skip) | next meaningful token |\n| `consume()` | yes | same as prior peek |\n\n**Risk:** recursive `peek()` on long whitespace runs could stack-deep on pathological input. Acceptable for demo envelopes (<4 KB)."}
